# Hola Hola :nam_hap: 

## 5.0 is fast approaching :fire: 

For miners this is a fundamental shift and will really mix up the subnet.  It's an opportunity for new entries to challenge the old guard and for miners to contribute to pushing forward automl in a meaningful way. 

Here be the branch which is close to finalised, if you want to take part **you must read this code** to know how to enter etc.  

* https://github.com/rayonlabs/G.O.D/tree/5.0

and here's a blog post with some nuggets: 

* https://medium.com/@weightswandering/gradients-5-0-opening-the-black-box-unlocking-enterprise-ai-training-34eb13121062

## How this will work on the 21st  🗓️  

  * We will fire out to miners 'Hey wanna join the comp?' (text and image are sep) - once you fire back you do, along with repo and hash, you'll be entered
  * Validators will then run your training code on selection of tasks
  * Your code will compete in group stages, then knockouts
  * Winners advance based on performance across test + synthetic datasets eval'd in the same way as we do now
  * The ultimate champion's AutoML script goes open source

## Emissions :take_my_money: 

  * Tournament will take up most of the emissions of the subnet
  * When tournament winners are below legacy performance on boss round tasks,  emissions redistribute:
    - For every 1%  that  legacy outperforms tourn  → 5% of tournament allocation gets redistributed
    - A quarter goes to legacy  miners.  the rest adds to burn
    - Legacy base emission starts at 25%, tourn starts at 50% (split 60/40 text and image)  - but will change overtime like the current task proportions 
  * Making it to higher tournament rounds = more emission weight
  * Defending champions get large emission advantages and must be beaten clearly to be knocked off the throne, simple param tweaks won't cut it - the initial defending champ will be basecode, so an easy win to get in now
* Any emission you gain from a tourn will remain until the next tourn is finish  🥕 
## What You Need  :laptop: 
 
  * **Public GitHub repo** with your training code
  * Implement `/training_repo/{task_type}` endpoint returning:
    ```json
    {
      "github_repo": "https://github.com/yourname/training-repo",
      "commit_hash": "abc123..."
    }```
  - Be ready to accept tournament invites on the 21st! We'll keep trying registered peeps until we have met a minimum entries

## Tournament Structure 🥊 

  - Group Stage: 6-8 miners per group, top performers advance
  - Knockouts: Head-to-head elimination
  - Boss Round: Winner must beat defending champ by 5%+ (across 3 tasks)

We will have a beaut of a dashboard showing how you fared with next steps to also wandb out all the training metrics as your training runs progress. 📊

## Selecting the tourn participants

One thing we don't want is to be evaluating 200 of essentially the same repo because a few miners have entered many times with tiny tweaks. 

So we'll cap the num initially at 32 per tourn (for each, text and image separately) based on the alpha stake per uid. 

The top 32 by alpha stake  at the time of asking if you want to enter, we will then make sure you maintain that amount of stake for the whole tourn. If you drop your stake during the comp, you'll be eliminated - soz.
